title: Norsepower Loan
author: Norsepower
pages:
#- Tutum Bank, G13 Tigerstaden.
26.03.2013 11:20
Norsepower loans 32d with 10% interest a week from Tutum Bank.
Norsepower must pay 10% of 32d a week and the amount loaned (32d), within the deadline (6 weeks, the 7th of May).

#- The loan is secured against the stone brick tower at -8984,-4369, Aristopolis. Tutum Bank has the right to reclaim that plot if Norsepower fails to pay within the six weeks. If the sale of the reclaimed property gains less than what Norsepower owes Tutum
#- Bank, Norsepower will still be responsible of paying back what hasn't been covered.
Norsepower is not allowed to sell/modify or in any way damage the property without permission from Tutum Bank, before the loan has been repaid. If this happens, a penalty
#- fee equal to the damages will be issued.
If Norsepower fails to pay within 6 weeks and wants to keep his/hers property, (s)he must pay a penalty fee of 3d.Then an additional week is added to the deadline. The same rules will apply for the extended
#- deadline.If Norsepower fails to pay within the deadline it’s theft.
This loan is seen as an asset for Tutum Bank and can therefore be sold.
By signing this book, Norsepower agreeees on all of the terms.
#- 